    "body": "> > Tried with moralis, same error. Tried hardhat version 2.8 and 2.7, same error. I am guessing the issue is in one of the dependencies.\r\n> \r\n> @asafyish You are correct. @fvictorio confirmed to me on Discord that this is an issue with the recent ethereumjs release.\r\n> \r\n> Although I may not be the most qualified to make this claim, I believe the cause to be the line here: https://github.com/ethereumjs/ethereumjs-monorepo/blob/master/packages/tx/src/eip1559Transaction.ts#L238-L240\r\n> \r\n> The eip1559Transaction.ts constructor always calls `this.common.isActivatedEIP(3860)`.\r\n> \r\n> However, Hardhat extends `isActivatedEIP` to always fail for any numbers other than 2930 or 1559: https://github.com/NomicFoundation/hardhat/blob/master/packages/hardhat-core/src/internal/hardhat-network/provider/transactions/ReadOnlyValidEIP1559Transaction.ts#L65-L77\r\n> \r\n> In any case, I was advised to use Yarn resolutions to downgrade to an earlier version of ethereumjs.\r\n\r\nUpgrading nodejs to v16.14.2 solved the problem for me.\r\nAlso sometimes, forking with the same parameters (for alchemy, moralis) more than one instance causes similar issues... Make sure you're forking from only once machine.",
